[2
Date: Sat. 15 Jan 2000, 6.00 p.m. GMT+1
From: Wolfgang PREISER <preiser@wildmail.com>
Source: The Wuerzburg Mission Hospital website <http://www.uni-
wuerzburg.de/missio/klinik/lassa.html> Translation by W. Preiser

Situation on 15 January 2000 at 11.00 a.m. (GMT+1)
It is with great regret that we have to inform you that the patient
suffering from Lassa fever has died on 15 January 2000 at 9.37 a.m. During
the preceding night there had been a rapid and progressive deterioration of
blood clotting with massive bleeding in all organs. The patient died from
multi-organ failure thus caused. The employees of the Mission Hospital wish
to express their condolences to the relatives.
After consultation with Professor Schmitz from the virological department
of the Tropical Institute in Hamburg (Bernhard Nocht- Institut,
http://www.bni.uni-hamburg.de) we inform you that, contrary to press
reports from 14 Jan 2000, the high virus load was unchanged in a sample
from the morning of 14 Jan 2000. Against expectations no antibodies were
detectable in that sample. According to Prof. Schmitz this might possibly
be a novel and very aggressive variant of the Lassa virus.
There continues to be NO risk of transmission to patients, visitors and
employees of the Mission Hospital nor for the inhabitants of Wuerzburg and
environs.
--
Dr. Wolfgang Preiser, DTM&H, DipRCPath
